ism’s future, where zinesters persistently and stubbornly carve out new spaces for what it means to be a revolutionary and a girl. Girl Zines takes zines seriously, asking what they can tell us about the inner lives of girls and women over the last twenty years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Feminism & Feminist Theory.2bisacsh  aGirl.  aabout.  aasking.  agirls.  ainner.  alast.  alives.  aover.  aseriously.  atakes.  atell.  athey.  atwenty.  awhat.  awomen.  ayears.  azines.1 aZeisler, Andi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZeisler, Andi.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081476751140uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814768501.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814768501423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814768501/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK